    "These findings are consistent with prior research highlighting the importance of non-cognitive factors (e.g., motivation) and learning strategies in language learning (Lin et al., 2017).",
    "Furthermore, 20 studies using SR investigated noncognitive elements in teacher education contexts where teachers' non-cognitive factors, such as intrinsic motivation, are strongly associated with their professional development (Maaranen et al., 2019).",
    "In the realm of educational subjects, SR has also occupied a pivotal within the domain of STEM and art education research.",
    "Within the STEM disciplines, researchers have employed this methodology to probe the impact of pedagogical strategies (13 articles), non-cognitive processing (10 articles), and cognitive processing (6 articles).",
